summary: An Ordinance submitting to the qualified voters of the City of Seattle at the general election to be held in said City Tuesday, March 2, 1915, the proposition of the issuance and sale by said City of its general bonds in the sum of Five Hundred Forty-five Thousand ($545,000.) Dollars, for the purpose of providing money for the construction of a bridge for the City of Seattle across Lake Union along the line of Eastlake Avenue produced northeasterly.
